<div id="comment_status_64449024" class="commentstatus"></div>
<div id="comment_64449024" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64449024" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64449024" name="comment_link_64449024" href="//yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23312660&amp;cid=64449024" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64449024)" >Re:</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64449024" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64449024); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>2</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~stabiesoft">stabiesoft</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~stabiesoft">( 733417 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64449024"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64449024">I couldn't find it. Almost universally what I saw was modern ABS outperforms humans with the only exception being the occasional race car driver. The response time is about 10:1 ABS:human. Humans take around 120ms to react, ABS 10. The one area that was found to be better without ABS is sand/gravel. But most of us are not driving on that in traffic. The other thing ABS allows is in a panic with the pedal to the floor, you can still steer. If you lock em up, you lost steering.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64449024">

</div>
